title: Grateful Dead Live at Compton Terrace Amphitheatre on 1982-07-25
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1/Dolby B) -> Sound Devices 744T (24bit/96k) -> Adobe Audition v1.5 -> Samplitude Professional v10.22 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step-> Franklin's Tower-> CC Rider, Bird Song, El Paso, Candyman, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Deal

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Samson & Delilah, Crazy Fingers-> Estimated Prophet-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Good Lovin', E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text: Southwestern Treat This is a nice show with a solid set list.  Among other tunes, love the Half-Step opener and 2nd half of 2nd set (excellent transition from Black Peter to Good Lovin.  Boys were getting geared up for a great East coast fall tour!

Blob Weird I was actually shedding a tear during Lost Sailor for a recently departed friend and lo and behold--Bobby comes out of nowhere with some line about freedom not comin' easy and a 25 cent cup of coffee!!   My tears were gone in a millisecond after hearing that one......Weir. Can't live with him, can't live without him!!  A true original.  Spot on recording and great show.

Great Groove Super fun stuff, especially dig the groovey pace of Samson! 
82 was truly solid!
